						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">Śaka 1451 (1530 A.D.)</hi></p>						

						<p>Records the plating of certain objects with gold and silver by <hi rend="bold">Anantāḻvār-Piḷḷai,</hi> son of <hi rend="bold">Śrīraṅgarājar</hi> of Uttaramēlūr Kuravaiśēri, praying for the success of the <hi rend="italic">digvijaya</hi> of <hi rend="bold">Achyutadēva-Mahārāya.</hi> Mentions Bhūpālarāyaṉtūkku. The details of date viz., <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1451, Virōdhi, Tai 8,</hi> correspond to <hi rend="bold">1530 A.D. January 4,</hi> but are insufficient for verification.</p>						

						</summary>
